s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"rtCampers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"WordPress anniversary\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://rtcamp.com/?p=149327\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:337:\"<p>WordPress our favourite software turned 13 years old. We celebrated it\'s birthday with a special cake and a small party in the office.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wordpress-teenager-13/\">WordPress is now a teenager!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Aditya Kane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2174:\"<p>Thirteen years ago in 2003, the first ever version of WordPress appeared, thanks to collaborative efforts of Matt Mullenweg and Mike Little. It was forked from b2/cafelog.</p>\n<p>Over the past 13 years from being regarded as mainly just a blogging software, it now powers over <a href=\"https://w3techs.com/technologies/history_overview/content_management/all/y\">26% of the web</a>.</p>\n<p>Today, our favourite CMS, turns a teenager and we celebrated it&#8217;s birthday with a special cake. The cake cutting honours went to Vaishali, Divyaraj and Dhaval, the youngest rtCampers around.</p>\n<p><strong>Fun Fact: </strong>Vaishali and Dhaval were of age 10 and Divyaraj was only 8 years old when WordPress was first released!</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-149333\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/WordPress-anniversary-cake.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress-anniversary-cake\" width=\"600\" height=\"521\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/WordPress-anniversary-cake.jpg 600w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/WordPress-anniversary-cake-400x347.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s all of us posing for a group selfie.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-149338\" src=\"https://cdn.rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/rtCampers-group-photo.jpg\" alt=\"rtCampers-group-photo\" width=\"600\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/rtCampers-group-photo.jpg 600w, https://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/rtCampers-group-photo-400x267.jpg 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>If you want to read the WordPress origins story, read more about it on the <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/book/blob/master/Content/Part%201/3-the-blogging-software-dilemma.md\">WordPress book</a>.</p>\n<p>You may like to read <a href=\"https://ma.tt/2003/01/the-blogging-software-dilemma/\">Matt&#8217;s blog post which started WordPress</a>!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com/blog/wordpress-teenager-13/\">WordPress is now a teenager!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://rtcamp.com\">rtCamp</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0